The paper is about interpreting word alignments in Neural Machine Translation (NMT) models, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes model-agnostic interpretation methods, which could be relevant to other areas of machine learning, such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The methods involve analyzing the saliency of model predictions, which could also relate to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses alignment visualization techniques, which could be similar to those used in computer vision, hence cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also a possible sub-category.
